# Orora Platform - Project Organization Rules

## Project Structure

- `/apps` - Frontend applications (mobile & web)
  - `/apps/gemura-mobile` - Gemura Flutter mobile app
  - `/apps/gemura-web` - Gemura Next.js web app
  - `/apps/orora-mobile` - Orora Flutter mobile app (future)
  - `/apps/orora-web` - Orora Next.js web app (future)
- `/backend` - Shared NestJS backend API
- `/packages` - Shared code libraries
- `/docs` - Documentation (organized by shared/gemura/orora)
- `/scripts` - Scripts (organized by shared/gemura/orora)
- `/docker` - Docker configurations
- `/database` - Database files

## Documentation Standards

- Shared docs in `/docs/shared` (API, architecture, deployment)
- App-specific docs in `/docs/gemura` or `/docs/orora`
- Doc filenames: **kebab-case** (e.g. `deployment-guide.md`). Directory indexes: `README.md`
- Each directory has a README.md; use clear headings and structure
- Canonical structure: see `docs/shared/structure.md`

## Script Organization

- Shared scripts → `/scripts/shared`
- Gemura-specific → `/scripts/gemura`
- Orora-specific → `/scripts/orora`

## Code Organization

- Backend: Feature-based modules in `backend/src/modules/`
- Mobile: Feature-based in `apps/*/lib/features/`
- Web: Feature-based in `apps/*/app/`
- Shared code in `/packages`

## Task Completion

- On completion of each task touching mobile code, run `flutter analyze` from the app directory and fix any new errors or warnings.

## Git

- When a feature is completed, commit and push with a clear message.
- Skip build artifacts, dependencies, and local-only files.
